[MK] case called at 9:47am. 
Defendant Corrine E Quest in court with Attorney Sylvie H Dahnert.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
This case is scheduled for Final Status-Scheduling Conference today and for Jury Trial next week, however Attorney Dahnert submits paperwork for the entry of a change-of-plea.
After a brief discussion about there being no plea agreement in this case, an adjournment is taken for Attorney Dahnert to meet with Ms. Quest.
recess 9:47am, reconvene 10:02am.
ADA Hall indicates that the State is joining in the plea agreement as set forth in the Criminal Case Settlement form. 
Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest " entered; factual basis stipulated including as to Repeater status; the Court accepts the plea, finds Ms. Quest guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.
The Court continues the Bond. 
recess 10:09am 

NEXT:  Sentencing Hearing on June 2nd at 11:00am- send notices

[MK] case called at 2:08pm. 
Defendant Corrine E Quest in court.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
The Court discloses that in the Court's former capacity as Jefferson County District Attorney, then-DA Wambach had contacts and communication with Ms. Quest and her mother as victims in a case.  Judge Wambach also knows Ms. Quest as a former school-classmate of his son.  The Court does not feel that any disqualification or recusal is needed.  
Ms. Quest indicates that she is in agreement with having this Court proceed in this case.  ADA Hall reserves the opportunity to raise a concern with this; she wishes to confer with DA Happ on this disclosure.

Service of Complaint admitted, reading waived, the charge and maximum penalties are recited
The Court finds probable cause to exist in the Criminal Complaint. 
The Court further discloses that in the Court's former capacity as Jefferson County District Attorney, attorneys that DA Wambach supervised did prosecute Ms. Quest in a 2006 case . The Court does not feel that any disqualification or recusal is needed as to this role.
Right to counsel given; constructive waiver of counsel warnings given
After Ms. Quest indicates that she wishes to be represented by an attorney, the Court adjourns the Initial Appearance. 

The Court requires a $2,500 Signature Bond, with conditions: 
--no possession or consumption of controlled substances without a valid prescription 
--to take all prescription drugs as prescribed
--no possession of hypodermic needles or syringes unless in possession of a valid prescription for these
--to go to the State Public Defenders Office this afternoon to arrange to have an eligibility evaluation done 
--to report to the Jefferson County Sheriff's Department today for booking
recess 2:20pm. 

NEXT:  Adjourned Initial Appearance on 9/22/15 at 2:00pm.
